Why Operator?
An Operator automates the full lifecycle of complex applications by encoding a human engineer's "runbook" directly into Kubernetes code. 
It moves you from basic deployments to self-healing, auto-scaling infrastructure that manages itself based on your specific business logic.
ie. It manages everything from initial deployment and configuration to ongoing updates, scaling, and failure recovery. 
Essentially, it acts as a "24/7 Virtual SRE" that keeps the application in its desired state without manual intervention.


