1.  Setup (RHEL 9.7 + CRI-O)

On a CRI-O cluster, you don't have the Docker daemon. You'll use the Container Tools module, 
which is the official RHEL way to handle OCI images.
  

# Install the RHEL Container Tools (Podman, Buildah, Skopeo)
sudo dnf install container-tools -y

# Link podman to docker so the Operator SDK's Makefile works out of the box
sudo dnf install podman-docker -y
sudo dnf install golang -y
sudo dnf install git -y

