Step 4: The Reconcile Logic (The "Expert" Part)

Open internal/controller/helloapp_controller.go. This is where you write the automation. You want to show your audience how to:

    Fetch the Custom Resource.

    Define a Deployment.

    Ensure the Deployment matches the Spec.

Go

func (r *HelloAppReconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error) {
    log := log.FromContext(ctx)

    // 1. Fetch the HelloApp instance
    helloApp := &webv1alpha1.HelloApp{}
    err := r.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, helloApp)
    if err != nil {
        return ctrl.Result{}, client.IgnoreNotFound(err)
    }

    // 2. Check if the deployment already exists, if not create it
    found := &appsv1.Deployment{}
    err = r.Get(ctx, types.NamespacedName{Name: helloApp.Name, Namespace: helloApp.Namespace}, found)
    if err != nil && errors.IsNotFound(err) {
        // Define a new deployment
        dep := r.deploymentForHelloApp(helloApp)
        log.Info("Creating a new Deployment", "Deployment.Namespace", dep.Namespace, "Deployment.Name", dep.Name)
        err = r.Create(ctx, dep)
        if err != nil {
            return ctrl.Result{}, err
        }
        return ctrl.Result{Requeue: true}, nil
    }

    // 3. Ensure the deployment size is the same as the spec
    size := helloApp.Spec.Size
    if *found.Spec.Replicas != size {
        found.Spec.Replicas = &size
        err = r.Update(ctx, found)
        if err != nil {
            return ctrl.Result{}, err
        }
    }

    return ctrl.Result{}, nil
}

5. Transitioning to Expert Patterns 
keep these RHEL/CRI-O specific insights in mind:
Finalizers (The Safety Net)

if your Operator creates a resource outside of Kubernetes (like an entry in a DNS server or a folder on your RHEL physical storage), a Finalizer prevents the CR from being deleted until that external resource is cleaned up. It's essentially a pre-delete hook.
Leader Election (High Availability)

On a multi-node RHEL cluster, you don't want two Operators fighting over the same resource.

    The Demo Tip: the main.go file where --leader-elect is defined. This uses a Lease object in K8s to ensure only one pod is active.

